         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15./1/81. ¶  ¶ I have to thank you, dear Sir Joseph, for sending me the copy of your last annual report, ¶  showing again the scope of the wide progressive labours of Kew. Will you allow me to draw yo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">81.01.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller 1871-81, f. 296.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15./1/81.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have to thank you, dear Sir Joseph, for sending me the copy of your last annual report,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker (1881).</p>
               </note> showing again the scope of the wide progressive labours of Kew. Will you allow me to draw your attention to the transfer of <name key="Landolphia">Landolphia</name> to Va[h]ea, effected in my enlarged edition of Wittstein's Chemistry of plants,<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Wittstein (1878), i.e. B78.06.09.</p>
               </note> and continued in the Calcutta and now also in the still further augmented Sydney edition of my select plants.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B80.13.07, B81.01.04.</p>
               </note> Both works must be very handy to any bot. establishment. I was surprised, that A. de Candolle in his "phytographi[e]"<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A. de Candolle (1880).</p>
               </note> took no notice whatever of my huge Museum of dried plants nor any thing else of my Department.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also M to A. de Candolle, 4 August 1880.</p>
               </note> I cannot understand it. I do not care for myself, but do not like to see my Department unjustly ignored, though I got accustomed already to that in many ways. This evening I saw Miss North<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Marianne North.</p>
               </note> after her voyage to West Australia, and bid her Adieu, as she will start for Tasmania in a few days. Her paintings of W.A. vegetation are grand. I particularly admired your fathers Euc. macrocarpa;<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Eucalyptus%20macrocarpa">Eucalyptus macrocarpa</name>
                     </seg>; Her painting is illustrated at <ref target="https://www.kew.org/mng/gallery/751.html"
                          rend="Internet%20link"
                          style="color: #0000ff; ">
                        <seg rend="Internet%20link" style="color: #0000ff; ">https://www.kew.org/mng/gallery/751.html</seg>
                     </ref> (accessed 20 December 2019).</p>
               </note> you probably have this brillant<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">brilliant?</p>
               </note> species at Kew, as I sent seeds repeatedly.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
